 ICPC Chairman, Prof. Bolaji Owasanoye. Photot: TWITTER/ NIQS  The Guardian investigation revealed that on March 15, 2019, the commission received a petition from Concerned Volunteers Forum of Nigerian Red Cross alleging financial impropriety in the state chapter of the society. Part of the petition read: “This is to bring to your notice the unfolding fraud perpetrated by the acting secretary of Nigerian Red Cross Society (NRCS), Adamawa State branch, Muhammad Saidu Bello, for your intervention.”  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .